# TARGET ARCHITECTURE (Sidecar)

```
Browser SPA (web-chat/)
    → nginx
        /api/v1/*     → Platform API (FastAPI) — auth, workspaces, files, RAG, admin
        /api/chat*    → Agent Gateway (web_chat :8643) — SSE + Hermes runner
        /             → SPA static assets
```

| Layer | Path | Responsibility |
|-------|------|----------------|
| **Platform Control Plane** | `platform-api/` | Register/login, workspaces, files, RAG, memory/skill APIs, admin |
| **Agent Gateway** | `gateway/platforms/web_chat.py`, `gateway/web/` | SSE chat, conversations, uploads, `WebChatAgentRunner` |
| **Hermes Runtime** | upstream (`run_agent.py`, tools) | Agent loop — **black box; no business coupling** |
| **Data** | PG + pgvector, Redis, MinIO, `web_workspaces/<user_id>/` | Control-plane DB + per-user sandbox FS |

**Scale:** ~50 users — simple operable stack over distributed complexity.

**LLM billing:** Delegated to **new-api**. `UpstreamProvisioner` auto-provisions per-user keys on register.

## MVP scope

**In:** register/login, workspace, chat, file upload + RAG, memory/skill UI, admin basics, web search.

**Out (unless explicitly approved):** OAuth/SSO, Stripe, multi-workspace, real-time push sync, OS sandbox, `delegate_task`, OCR, separate vector DB, Hermes core edits.

